scaldex is a local CLI measurement tool for Codex instruction packages.
It can invoke the Codex CLI and OpenAI or Codex services when the user
starts a paid benchmark run. Those external services, names, APIs and
outputs remain subject to their own terms, policies and availability.

Codex and OpenAI API keys are user-owned. scaldex does not provide a
shared API key and does not write the key into generated reports, history
or configuration files.

scaldex reports benchmark evidence. Results are task-specific measurement
evidence, not a guarantee of future Codex behaviour, software quality,
cost savings, legal compliance or operational suitability.
